<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
In metal_shmem_open, the local iterator pointer is declared as 'struct metal_page_size *ps;' but throughout the loop ps is only read (ps->page_size, ps->page_shift, ps->mmap_flags) and not modified. Therefore the pointer could and should be const-qualified (e.g. 'const struct metal_page_size *ps'). Declaring it non-const violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13. (To fix, make ps const and update metal_shmem_try_map to accept 'const struct metal_page_size *ps' if necessary.)
</scenario>

